Swedish mining and metals groupBoliden AB &lt;BLDS.ST> said the takeover of the U.S.Allis-Chalmers Corp's &lt;AH.O> mining machinery division made itthe world's leading maker of such equipment.    President Kjell Nilsson, announcing the 600 mln crown deal,told a news conference Boliden would now become a trulyinternational concern with operations in Brazil, Chile andother big minerals-producing nations.    He said the Allis-Chalmers' division, accounting for some50 pct of the U.S. Group's sales, would fit in well intoBoliden. REUTER&#3;